Euclidean Algorithm for finding GCD of two numbers is done using a recursive function. 
The steps for finding the GCD using Euclidean Algorithm are:
1. Assume there exists two numbers a, b
2. a mod b = reminder
3. Let a=b and b=reminder
4. Repeat the above two steps until a mod b becomes 0
5. The value of b will be GCD after the 4th step

The implementation of the above steps in recursion is as follows: 
int gcd(int a, int b){
    if(b==0)
        return a;
    else
        return gcd(b,a%b);
}

To avoid these lines of code, C++ has the built-in function __gcd() in the header file <algorithm>.

Eg: cout<<__gcd(18,27); //Output: 9

